lines.text: Well, that's-that's all right... only, please, don't call me "Cuthbert" any more.
[Cuthbert and Swede scare off a stagecoach bandit who had been searching through a stolen mailbag]
I got a letter with the funniest name what you ever heard - Cuthbert Chauncy Dale.
[Buck rips the letter from Olaf's hands and opens it]
Oh, but land sakes, you can't do that!
No, but that letter happens to belong to me.
But I thought your name was Tom!
Say, listen Swede. My name is Cuthbert Chauncy Dale. And if you ever mention it to anybody or peep about it again, I'm gonna work you over plenty!
OK, Boss, I swear I'll never tell anyone a terrible thing like that.
